Test Case 1: We can build 3 complete layers. Layer 1 requires 1 brick, Layer 2 requires 2 bricks, Layer 3 requires 3 bricks. Total bricks used = 1 + 2 + 3 = 6.
The 4th layer requires 4 bricks, but only 2 are left. Therefore, the maximum number of complete layers is 3.
